definition.value:
A journal note to document the digital encounter.
Can be XHTML formatted text.
In the VKP project in Norway the note is used for: 
Response summary: A text describing the resolution of the digital-Encounter event

Example:
~~~
{
      "url":"http://ehelse.no/fhir/StructureDefinition/vkp-annotation-v06",
      "extension": [
          {
              "url":"note",
             "valueAnnotation":{
                  "authorReference":{
                      "identifier":{
                          "system":"urn:oid:2.16.578.1.12.4.1.4.1",
                          "value":"04056600324"
                     },
                      "display":"Magnar Koman"
                  },
                  "time":"2018-06-25T08:00:00.936Z",
                  "text":"Selve teksten til journalnotatet."
              }
          }
      ]
}
~~~

When a journal note is to document the digital encounter in the EHR it needs a string identifying who registered the note. A signature of who registered the information should be present in all events, even when there is no text in the journal note.

Can be XHTML formatted text.
In the VKP project in Norway the signature is used for: 
Signature: Name of author plus a system specific signature identifying the user who submitted the Composition (user name in the system).

Example:
~~~
{
   "url":"http://ehelse.no/fhir/StructureDefinition/vkp-annotation-v06",
      "extension": [
          {
              "url":"signature",
              "valueAnnotation":{
                 "time":"2018-06-25T08:00:00.936Z",
                 "text":"Magnar Koman (signatur)"
             }
          }
      ]
}
~~~

Refernce to the individual that participated in the encounter, usually health care provider. Identified using Norwegian national id number (fødselsnummer).
The Name of the participant should be given in the subject.display element.

Example: 
~~~~
"participant": [
   {
      "individual":{
         "identifier":{
            "system":"urn:oid:2.16.578.1.12.4.1.4.1",
            "value":"04056600324"
         },
         "display":"Magnar Koman"
      }
   }
]
~~~~

comment.value:
Virtual encounters can be recorded in the Encounter by specifying a location reference to a location of type "kind" such as "client's home" and an encounter.class = "virtual".

VKP Example:
~~~
 "location": [
        {
            "location":{
                "display":"rom24 @ sykehjem"
            }
        }
    ]
~~~
